Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.02,0:00:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Trisha?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.56,0:00:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Trisha? Trisha? You're kidding me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.86,0:00:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you sleeping in a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.36,0:00:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't you scold me like you usually do?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.03,0:00:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Olga-Marie...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.28,0:00:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Her head is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.58,0:00:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Contact the conductor!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.29,0:00:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.71,0:00:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a distressing turn of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.50,0:00:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you guys do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.96,0:00:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It must be you, Karabo!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.30,0:00:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.72,0:00:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy Church guys are magus killers!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.51,0:00:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately not.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.72,0:00:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it be all right if I performed the autopsy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.10,0:00:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm used to seeing corpses of this nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.77,0:00:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.90,0:00:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.78,0:00:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You. Take her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.61,0:00:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.70,0:01:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They quite readily allowed him to perform the autopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.25,0:01:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Magi killing each other is a common occurrence aboard this train.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.54,0:01:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the management won't concern themselves with each one.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.63,0:01:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-responsibility is fundamental.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.13,0:01:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.13,0:01:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you one thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.64,0:01:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.89,0:01:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You are a member of the Holy Church. Don't you find magi despicable?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.52,0:01:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I feel all magi should have their souls burned in purgatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.32,0:01:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's a different matter from this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.28,0:01:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The Black Keys bequeathed to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.32,0:01:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is not for piercing a young girl mourning the falling of a brethren.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.83,0:01:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems you really have strange ties to matters of this nature,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.75,0:01:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord El-Melloi II.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.75,0:01:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The same can be said for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.00,0:01:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been aboard the train the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.96,0:01:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean I have no alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.13,0:02:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You know well that such concepts can't be applied to magi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.97,0:02:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.89,0:02:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We were aboard the train, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.06,0:02:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I was outside with Karabo!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.11,0:02:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There were several other magi outside, so I'm sure I can get testimonies!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.65,0:02:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no doubt that the time of death is within one hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.87,0:02:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Cause of death is shock from beheading.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.87,0:02:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no traces of a scuffle,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.66,0:02:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so the perpetrator must've killed her in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.96,0:02:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But why did the perpetrator take her head?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.21,0:02:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She had the Mystic Eyes of Premonition.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.92,0:02:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I witnessed it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.84,0:02:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.92,0:02:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That means the perpetrator took her entire head
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.84,0:02:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for the purpose of taking her Mystic Eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.93,0:02:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Extracting Mystic Eyes from the head they took with them...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.18,0:02:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Is such a thing possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.14,0:02:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's aboard this Rail Zeppelin, that's a simple task.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.90,0:02:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, I'd like to perform an autopsy myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.03,0:02:57.07,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{OP}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.37,0:04:26.41,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{Episode}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you perhaps possess perception-type Mystic Eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.62,0:04:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you think that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.04,0:04:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Considering your age, it's more natural to think
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.01,0:04:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that the reason you're here is not to buy Mystic Eyes but to sell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.13,0:04:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you volunteer to do an autopsy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.01,0:04:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because you felt your Mystic Eyes were effective for that purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.68,0:04:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like I can't hide it from you, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.48,0:04:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,My eyes are the Mystic Eyes of Past Vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.31,0:05:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He showed me its powers earlier, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.48,0:05:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not convenient enough to always be able to specify time and location, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.53,0:05:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean the initiative is with the Mystic Eyes and not with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.20,0:05:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Lately, my Mystic Eyes have been dragging me into visions more often.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.92,0:05:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I boarded this train to part ways with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.05,0:05:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, were you able to see the perpetrator?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.55,0:05:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I couldn't see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.93,0:05:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There might have been some kind of protection working.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.39,0:05:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see how she was sitting here in this chair,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.06,0:05:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but the conditions right around the beheading was vague, and I couldn't see clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.77,0:05:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, the situation might've been vague for Trisha Fellows herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.65,0:05:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.74,0:05:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If she'd noticed, she surely would've taken some measures.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.41,0:05:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,At the least, she would have warned Olga-Marie as her subsidiary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.87,0:05:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means her death and its perpetrator...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.58,0:06:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,were not in either the Premonition or Past Vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.92,0:06:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He was invisible from both the past and the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if it was a man invisible to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.76,0:06:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have no guarantee that I'm telling the truth to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.43,0:06:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but I'd like to put my faith in people like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.14,0:06:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe those are words of a Lord of the Clock Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.77,0:06:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mystic Eyes are not techniques but innate characteristics.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.73,0:06:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And if so, they should regulate how one lives, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.11,0:06:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, humans are slaves to what they can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.53,0:06:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The world that we see can't be shared with anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.83,0:06:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw a friend become trapped within the dreams of Mystic Eyes the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.84,0:06:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you see the past means that you can't live in the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.55,0:06:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I have not once lived in the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.76,0:06:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor, Miss Olga-Marie has woken up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.19,0:07:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to make Animusphere owe El-Melloi a favor with something like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.23,0:07:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no such intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.36,0:07:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,For me, this is something like a creed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.90,0:07:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A creed?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.36,0:07:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Once, when I was still immature,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.07,0:07:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,there was someone who said my immaturity was a sign of military might.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.00,0:07:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"Glory lies beyond the horizon."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.50,0:07:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I was struggling because I was seeking something beyond my reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.71,0:07:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And someday, willing or not,\NI would discover my own path.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.43,0:07:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He kept telling me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.22,0:07:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, young ones yet to discover their paths unnecessarily losing their lives
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.81,0:07:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is something I can't allow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.15,0:07:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you told that during the Holy Grail War?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.40,0:07:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps by the Servant you summoned?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.45,0:07:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.24,0:07:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How ridiculous! A familiar influencing you? You're mistaking the means for the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.74,0:07:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.66,0:08:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet humans still become slaves to what they see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.87,0:08:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Gray, I'm trusting her with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.21,0:08:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go negotiate with the conductor to prepare a new room for Lady Olga-Marie.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.47,0:08:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Caules.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.59,0:08:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.55,0:08:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.31,0:08:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.06,0:08:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, have some cocoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.56,0:08:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what is that weird Lord to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.86,0:08:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For me,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.24,0:08:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,he's a very good mentor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.12,0:08:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.49,0:08:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not a magus, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.00,0:08:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Even then, I'll be all right if I keep up with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.08,0:08:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how I feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.42,0:08:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.13,0:08:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.34,0:08:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You're pretty weird yourself, following such a weird guy like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.43,0:09:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.60,0:09:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.69,0:09:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep, Shishigou is over at the department head office in Slar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.98,0:09:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.03,0:09:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the card I gave you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.90,0:09:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, please don't hesitate to use it. After all, it will only increase your debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.04,0:09:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.75,0:09:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a troublesome elder brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.01,0:09:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you up to this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.34,0:09:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, are you interested in Policies? Or myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.72,0:09:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's not play dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.68,0:09:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You, the one who retrieved documents about this train from the Codrington Estate, are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.56,0:09:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't think you have no actual reason to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.73,0:09:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember Gurdoa Davenant?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.90,0:09:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he was a pesky old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.49,0:10:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who sponsored Gurdoa,\Nand the one who sponsored Codrington...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.66,0:10:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems it was the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.66,0:10:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that person is involved with Rail Zeppelin?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.12,0:10:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't go that far.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.54,0:10:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, it's your job to deduce the answer, isn't it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.63,0:10:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.18,0:10:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no traces.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.35,0:10:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Same results with Spiritual Evocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.35,0:10:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like the perpetrator did a good job of taking the relic out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.19,0:10:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it didn't break past the bounded field.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.36,0:10:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Missie Hyena?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.70,0:10:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What's with that nickname?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.16,0:10:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Stealing spells is a specialty of the Edelfelt Family, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.37,0:10:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't deny that. From that viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.67,0:10:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems the perpetrator had a spare key\Nfor this bounded field to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.92,0:10:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it was an inside job after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.34,0:11:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are getting interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.55,0:11:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost the time that the perpetrator specified.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.43,0:11:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Escaping to the outside world is impossible, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.06,0:11:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.94,0:11:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This train is halfway to the underworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.77,0:11:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be very difficult to enter from the outside or escape from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.95,0:11:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's what the invitations are for.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.66,0:11:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct. You can say that the invitations are keys to the underworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.41,0:11:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, if we create a gate using an invitation from this side,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.17,0:11:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we can use an adaptation of Touko Travel, and—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.71,0:11:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.04,0:11:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.42,0:11:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bad habit for me to become so lost in something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.51,0:11:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There are clouds now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.47,0:11:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.88,0:11:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Gray!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.51,0:11:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Something is approaching!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.10,0:11:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Master, over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.90,0:12:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you really did show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.90,0:12:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I mock someone for plunging in as a fool even if it's a trap?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.82,0:12:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Or should I praise him for having the fortitude capable of routing the enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.16,0:12:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you the one who stole the relic from Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.88,0:12:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a vassal of the burglar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.38,0:12:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Then give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.38,0:12:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Gray!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.27,0:12:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Who...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.31,0:12:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.94,0:12:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.32,0:12:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheap, narrow-minded, gloomy and stubborn. A poor riser.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.03,0:12:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like you've seen the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.95,0:12:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but in the end, you're the one who disturbed things the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.66,0:12:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How was that? All of that applies to you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.29,0:12:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They said Iskandar served under him, though temporarily,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.75,0:13:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so I wondered what kind of magus I'd see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.84,0:13:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But this good-for-nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.59,0:13:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.34,0:13:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,did not have him serve under me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.84,0:13:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the King of Conqueror's subject!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.31,0:13:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A Subject? You?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.18,0:13:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We shared the same dream,\Nand I tried to keep pace with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.23,0:13:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And he commanded me to live!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.98,0:13:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.48,0:13:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I lured you out here simply because I had my curiosity prioritized.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.49,0:13:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.53,0:13:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that ended up being in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.74,0:13:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I've had enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.66,0:13:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm disgusted! There's only so much you can take before you're fed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.00,0:13:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, die!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.21,0:13:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You are...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.13,0:13:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember! Simply having combat skills doesn't make you a warrior!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.55,0:13:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Becoming a warrior is an issue concerning everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.85,0:13:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Body, will and soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.68,0:13:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.72,0:13:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A Servant!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.68,0:13:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a Ghost Liner!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.27,0:13:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The materialization of a Heroic Spirit\Nengraved into human history!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.44,0:14:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mentor is a bit slow in giving you a warning!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.70,0:14:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an interesting stunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.95,0:14:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you absorb some of my magical energy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.79,0:14:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This is rather fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.37,0:14:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show you something good, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.04,0:14:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Mystic Eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.34,0:14:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe you guys call it the "Noble Color of Coercion."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.42,0:14:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it a fitting end for this setting?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.51,0:14:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My god Dionysus values madness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.26,0:14:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,An image of mentor and apprentice killing one another seemed truly fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.14,0:14:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, those glasses nullify Mystic Eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.57,0:14:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Why you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.65,0:14:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, Gray!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.19,0:14:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Serious? Are you serious? Hold on a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.24,0:14:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so you cleansed your magic circuit\Nwith that scythe. Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.33,0:15:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I had hoped you'd be decent enough to settle your own score, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.38,0:15:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.67,0:15:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's already too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.38,0:15:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad, bad, bad! Gray, not that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.59,0:15:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything but that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.22,0:15:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.76,0:15:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.10,0:15:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.93,0:15:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Gordius Wheel?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.64,0:15:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Master,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.23,0:15:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.32,0:15:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Iskandar's Noble Phantasm!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.48,0:15:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Hephaestion!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.32,0:15:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the primary confidante of the greatest King of Conquerors in history, Iskandar!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.91,0:15:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.29,0:15:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You have absolutely no qualifications to become one of Iskandar's subjects!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.67,0:15:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Gray. Rave.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't, Gray!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.59,0:15:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Using that at an unsecure foothold like this won't leave us unharmed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.76,0:15:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave this to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.27,0:16:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor! Miss Gray!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.23,0:16:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Caules...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.28,0:16:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Are both of you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.03,0:16:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not coming after us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.75,0:16:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Unleashing something like that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.46,0:16:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,means she'd be fighting the Mystic Eyes Collection Train itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.67,0:16:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a bit flustered.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.38,0:16:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt some magical energy in the lightning and came out to look
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.42,0:16:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and saw that commotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.42,0:16:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm so happy to see you, Caules.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.85,0:16:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you cut your hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.10,0:16:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I amplified a control spell with the magical energy stored in my hair
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.02,0:16:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the thunder can flow down into the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.11,0:16:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, hair symbolizes snakes, an incarnation of lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.78,0:16:53.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Master, who in the world was that Servant?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.74,0:16:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She had toned things down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.45,0:16:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If she really wanted to kill us,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.08,0:17:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,such cheap tricks wouldn't be good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.12,0:17:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No, in the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.87,0:17:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,how did she summon that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.67,0:17:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is there...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.75,0:17:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a confidante to the king...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.51,0:17:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,whom I've never seen before?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.09,0:17:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.89,0:17:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you can't leave people alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.22,0:17:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so why do you go off on your own and leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.31,0:17:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Please stand aside!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.52,0:17:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a terrible burn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.15,0:17:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll use the Primeval Battery!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.65,0:17:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll adjust the bioelectric currents
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.82,0:17:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to heighten Professor's own healing powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.37,0:17:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll activate his Od as much as I can, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.24,0:17:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Will he be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.33,0:17:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be fine, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.91,0:17:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.71,0:17:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.79,0:17:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Was he actually attacked by Trisha's murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.05,0:17:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that we were attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.30,0:17:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But it has something to do with just us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.85,0:18:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.35,0:18:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm disgusted!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.68,0:18:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're an apprentice to a magus,\Nyou need to be prepared for something like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.03,0:18:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, why don't you use this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.99,0:18:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.24,0:18:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Druid Elixir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.91,0:18:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Druid Elixir?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.16,0:18:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Panacea, the cure-all?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.79,0:18:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Trisha handed it to me just in case,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.67,0:18:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but since I have no way to use it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.67,0:18:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.26,0:18:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Look here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.42,0:18:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, Animusphere no longer owes anything to El-Melloi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.43,0:18:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all! Good night!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.18,0:18:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But to think, here I am, pretending to be detectives with a magician like you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.69,0:18:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How I have fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.90,0:18:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You say that, but you were acting rather lively.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.07,0:18:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not often you can rummage through the central core of Modern Magecraft Theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.16,0:19:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The previous department head has so many mysteries as is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.08,0:19:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean Kayneth El-Melloi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.45,0:19:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.04,0:19:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.25,0:19:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the Lord of Mineralogy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.71,0:19:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't even know that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.71,0:19:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The Clock Tower is a place that's difficult for me to approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.09,0:19:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, who was the predecessor?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.47,0:19:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The predecessor wasn't a Lord to begin with—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.30,0:19:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.64,0:19:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, my elder brother was seriously injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.64,0:19:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, consider your request itself to still be ongoing,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.77,0:19:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,considering how Animusphere is making a move, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.98,0:19:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Just get out of my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.48,0:19:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}I only have need for one person, Reines El-Melloi Archisorte!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.07,0:19:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I have to hang up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.16,0:19:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady, what is the meaning of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.37,0:19:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,For starters, can you wipe up all the blood you've coughed up, Mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.00,0:19:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.21,0:19:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Melvin Waynes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.92,0:19:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My elder brother is not present, but I can take your message.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.80,0:20:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I'm here for!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.47,0:20:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell me Waver had gotten aboard the Rail Zeppelin?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.60,0:20:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no need to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.18,0:20:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No, just by being his best friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.02,0:20:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm obligated to at least hear that much!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.31,0:20:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, I myself heard of the news several days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.61,0:20:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And you didn't tag along, Reines?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.44,0:20:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though it seems so much fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.40,0:20:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can tell, I'm rather busy doing my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.45,0:20:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I have no choice but to go by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.79,0:20:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Go by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.25,0:20:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone has to record Waver breaking into tears, so I'll go do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.17,0:20:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,See this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.46,0:20:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the financial powers of the Waynes Family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.84,0:20:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As you'd expect from Panacea,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.88,0:20:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,by combining it with the Primeval Battery,\Nwe can accelerate cell activation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.68,0:20:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,With this...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.93,0:20:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you should rest a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.52,0:20:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to apply medicine on him anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.27,0:20:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.69,0:21:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Caules, you're really calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.07,0:21:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. When my big sister said she was going to renounce being a magus,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.57,0:21:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I might've gained some courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.37,0:21:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Your big sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.41,0:21:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,My big sister was what you'd call a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.41,0:21:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But she suddenly renounced being a magus
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.46,0:21:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and even gave up her magic crest
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.59,0:21:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\t(1605,1730,\c&HE3E3E3&\3c&HE3E3E3&\4c&HE3E3E3&)}before leaving the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.84,0:21:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the entire family was in a riot from the top all the way down.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.68,0:21:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There even were guys who tried to kill someone ordinary like me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.09,0:21:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so she would resume being the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.81,0:21:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, that was a strange story, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.61,0:21:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. You'll become powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.44,0:21:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,More than your big sister, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.28,0:21:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Master picked you out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.75,0:21:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,God, I beg you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.17,0:22:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't give Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.17,0:22:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,such a lonely way to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.02,0:22:10.06,Default,chptr,0,0,0,,{ED}
